14 leaving victims, including pedestrians and cyclists without the opportunity to present victim
15 impact statements; and
16 WHEREAS, Georgia's infrastructure budgets and plans should be reviewed to ensure
17 investments are being made in safety countermeasures to reduce roadway fatalities and
18 injuries; and
19 WHEREAS, study of Georgia law is needed to determine appropriate penalties for harming
20 vulnerable roadway users and to improve enforcement mechanisms, including revisions to
21 violations of law handled in traffic violations bureaus.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE:
23 (1) Creation of Senate study committee. There is created the Senate Study Committee
24 on Vulnerable Roadway Users.
25 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of the following members
26 to be appointed by the President of the Senate:
27 (A) Five members of the Senate;
28 (B) The commissioner of transportation or his or her designee;
29 (C) A member of Propel ATL;
30 (D) A member of GO Georgia; and
31 (E) A municipal traffic court judge.
32 The President of the Senate shall designate a legislative member of the committee as
33 chairperson of the committee.
34 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
35 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
36 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
